{"innormalQuit":false,"windows":[{"path":"/run/media/rubait/storage/@personal/important/SKILL.md","untitledId":1776413761583,"type":"","hasUnsaved":true,"scrollPos":2700,"useCRLF":false,"finalNewline":true,"syncDate":1776413822259,"mountFolder":"/run/media/rubait/storage/@personal/important","content":"---\nname: omarchy-knowledge\ndescription: Deep knowledge base for OmarchyOS (Arch Linux + Hyprland, by DHH/Basecamp). Use this skill whenever Rubait asks about OmarchyOS, Hyprland config, Waybar, Omarchy themes, omarchy-update, keybindings, dotfiles, system customization, looknfeel.conf, monitors, shell tools, or anything related to his Linux desktop environment. Also trigger when debugging display issues (GDK_SCALE), Hyprland errors, or any question mentioning \"omarchy\", \"hyprland.conf\", \"waybar\", \"walker\", or \"omarchy menu\".\n---\n\n# OmarchyOS Knowledge Base\n\nOmarchy = opinionated Arch Linux + Hyprland setup by DHH (Basecamp). \"Omakase computing\" — strong curated defaults, minimal necessary configuration. Installed via ISO. Underneath it's vanilla Arch — pacman, yay, AUR all work normally.\n\n---\n\n## Core Architecture — The Two-Directory Model\n\nThis is THE most important concept.\n\n| Directory | Owner | Rule |\n|---|---|---|\n| `~/.local/share/omarchy` | Omarchy upstream | NEVER edit directly. Changes will conflict with `omarchy-update`. |\n| `~/.config` | Yours | All customization goes here. Safe across updates. |\n\n**Override pattern:** If you need to change something Omarchy owns in `~/.local/share/omarchy`, find the corresponding file in `~/.config` and override it there. Never fork the source.\n\nIf you must edit `~/.local/share/omarchy` directly, commit changes first or `omarchy-update` will fail/conflict.\n\n---\n\n## Key Config Files in `~/.config`\n\n| File | Controls |\n|---|---|\n| `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf` | Main Hyprland config. Sources other files below. |\n| `~/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` | All keybindings. Edit here, not hyprland.conf. |\n| `~/.config/hypr/monitors.conf` | Monitor resolution, position, scale (`GDK_SCALE`). |\n| `~/.config/hypr/looknfeel.conf` | Rounding, gaps, borders, visual style. |\n| `~/.config/hypr/input.conf` | Keyboard options (compose key, kb_options). |\n| `~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf` | Idle/sleep behaviour. |\n| `~/.config/hypr/hyprlock.conf` | Lock screen — symlinked to active theme. |\n| `~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc` | Waybar layout. Edit freely. |\n| `~/.config/waybar/style.css` | Waybar CSS — **symlinked to active theme**. Changes overwritten on theme switch. |\n| `~/.config/walker/config.toml` | App launcher (Walker) config. |\n| `~/.config/alacritty/alacritty.toml` | Terminal config. |\n| `~/.config/uwsm/default` | Default `$EDITOR` and terminal. Requires Hyprland restart after change. |\n| `~/.config/omarchy/themes/` | Your custom themes live here. |\n| `~/.bashrc` | Shell aliases, functions, exports. **Never overwritten by updates.** Safe place for all shell customization. |\n| `~/.XCompose` | Emoji and text autocompletion. Run `omarchy-restart-xcompose` after editing. |\n\n**Access any config fast:** `Super + Alt + Space` → Setup → Configs → [process]. Auto-restarts the process after `:wq`.\n\n---\n\n## Hyprland Config Hierarchy\n\n```\n~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf\n  sources → bindings.conf     (keybindings)\n  sources → monitors.conf     (display setup)\n  sources → looknfeel.conf    (visual tweaks)\n  sources → input.conf        (keyboard/mouse)\n  sources → hypridle.conf     (idle)\n```\n\nBest practice for Rubait: append `source = ~/.config/hypr/custom.conf` to `hyprland.conf` and put all personal overrides in `custom.conf`. That way upstream changes to `hyprland.conf` don't eat your customizations.\n\n**After any Hyprland config change:** Run `hyprctl configerrors` to catch syntax issues before reloading. Reload with `hyprctl reload` or `Super + Esc` (restarts UWSM/Hyprland).\n\n---\n\n## Waybar — Rubait-Specific Rules\n\n- Signals **7–10 are reserved by OmarchyOS**. Custom modules must use signal **11+**.\n- `~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc` is yours — edit freely.\n- `~/.config/waybar/style.css` is **theme-symlinked** — any direct CSS edits are wiped on theme switch. Strategy: add a secondary CSS `@import` at the bottom of the theme's CSS, or manage style in a file that isn't theme-managed.\n- In `exec` and `on-click` fields: use `$HOME` not `~` — Waybar does not expand `~`.\n- For click actions that need user input: use `omarchy-launch-floating-terminal-with-presentation`.\n- Tray icons hidden by default behind expander. To show all: change `group/tray-expander` → `tray` in `config.jsonc`.\n\n---\n\n## Theme System\n\n- 17 built-in themes. Switch via `Super + Ctrl + Shift + Space` or Omarchy Menu → Style → Theme.\n- Themes live at `~/.local/share/omarchy/themes/` (upstream, read-only).\n- **Custom themes:** Copy a theme to `~/.config/omarchy/themes/[theme-name]`. It auto-appears in the theme menu. Never modify themes in `~/.local/share/omarchy/themes/`.\n- Main theme file: `colors.toml` — defines color set that auto-generates configs for Alacritty/Ghostty/Kitty, btop, Chromium, Hyprland, Hyprlock, Mako, SwayOSD, Walker, Waybar.\n- Cycle wallpapers within theme: `Super + Ctrl + Space`.\n- Obsidian theme must be set manually inside Obsidian (Appearance → Themes → Omarchy).\n- Light mode: drop empty file `light.mode` in theme root.\n- Icon color matching: add `icons.theme` file with Yaru variant name.\n- Distribute theme: push to public git, install via Omarchy Menu → Install → Theme → [git URL]. Name as `omarchy-[themename]-theme`.\n\n---\n\n## GDK_SCALE — Critical for Rubait's Setup\n\nOmarchyOS defaults to `GDK_SCALE=2` (assumes HiDPI/retina display).\n\n**Rubait runs a standard 1080p/standard-DPI monitor on EliteDesk.** This makes GTK apps render oversized.\n\n**Fix:**\n```ini\n# ~/.config/hypr/monitors.conf or hyprland.conf\nenv = GDK_SCALE,1\n```\nAlso add to `~/.bashrc`:\n```bash\nexport GDK_SCALE=1\n```\nSpotify: use `Ctrl + Minus` / `Ctrl + Plus` to manually adjust its zoom regardless of GDK_SCALE.\n\n---\n\n## Monitor Config (Multi-Machine Portable SSD Use)\n\n```ini\n# ~/.config/hypr/monitors.conf\n# Specific monitor by name (run `hyprctl monitors` to get name):\nmonitor=HDMI-A-1,1920x1080@100,0x0,1\n\n# Fallback for unknown/any monitor — ESSENTIAL for portable SSD use:\nmonitor=DP-3,1920x1080@100,auto,1\n```\n\nThe fallback `monitor=,preferred,auto,1` ensures any machine Rubait boots on gets sane defaults automatically. Without it, unknown monitors may get no output.\n\n---\n\n## Updates\n\n- **Always use:** `Update > Omarchy` in Omarchy Menu — pulls latest code + runs migrations + updates packages.\n- **Never use:** `pacman -Syu` or `yay -Syu` directly — skips Omarchy migrations, can break configs.\n- Update channels: `stable` (default) → `RC` → `edge` → `dev`. Switch via `Update > Channel`.\n- Rollback: restart and pick the pre-update snapshot in the GRUB/systemd-boot menu.\n- Nuclear reset: `omarchy-reinstall` — restores all default configs (overwrites your `~/.config` Omarchy changes).\n- Per-config reset: `Update > Config` in Omarchy Menu.\n- Debug: `omarchy-debug` — generates shareable diagnostic output.\n\n---\n\n## Shell Customization\n\n`~/.bashrc` is the safe zone. Add aliases, functions, exports here. Never overwritten by updates.\n\nOmarchy's default shell is **bash**. (zsh presence = legacy leftover from old installs — `.zshrc` is safely deletable if present from a previous setup).\n\n**Omarchy-shipped shell tools:**\n\n| Tool | Purpose | Key usage |\n|---|---|---|\n| `fzf` | Fuzzy finder | `ff` (fuzzy file find), `Ctrl+R` (history) |\n| `zoxide` | Smart `cd` | `cd oma` jumps to any prev-visited dir matching \"oma\" |\n| `ripgrep` | File content search | `rg pattern path/` |\n| `eza` | Better `ls` | aliased as `ls`, `lt` (nested), `lsa` (with hidden), `lta` |\n| `fd` | Better `find` | `fd filename` |\n| `try` | Experiment manager | Date-stamped dirs in `~/Work/tries` |\n\n---\n\n## Key Hotkeys Reference\n\n**Meta:**\n- `Super + K` — Show all hotkeys\n- `Super + Alt + Space` — Omarchy Menu (primary control panel)\n- `Super + Space` — App launcher (Walker)\n- `Super + Escape` — System menu (suspend/restart/logout)\n\n**Window management:**\n- `Super + Return` — Terminal\n- `Super + Alt + Return` — Tmux terminal\n- `Super + Shift + Return` — Browser\n- `Super + W` — Close window\n- `Super + F` — Fullscreen\n- `Super + T` — Toggle tiling/floating\n- `Super + L` — Toggle layout (dwindle ↔ scrolling)\n- `Super + J` — Toggle horizontal/vertical split\n\n**Workspaces:**\n- `Super + 1/2/3/4` — Jump to workspace\n- `Super + Shift + 1/2/3/4` — Move window to workspace\n- `Super + Tab` / `Super + Shift + Tab` — Next/prev workspace\n\n**App shortcuts:**\n- `Super + Shift + N` — Neovim\n- `Super + Shift + D` — LazyDocker\n- `Super + Shift + O` — Obsidian\n- `Super + Shift + F` — File manager\n\n**Clipboard (unified — works in terminal too):**\n- `Super + C` — Copy\n- `Super + V` — Paste\n- `Super + Ctrl + V` — Clipboard history\n\n**Capture:**\n- `Print Screen` — Screenshot\n- `Alt + Print Screen` — Screen record (toggle)\n- `Super + Print Screen` — Color picker\n- `Super + Ctrl + C` — Capture menu\n\n**Notifications:**\n- `Super + ,` — Dismiss latest\n- `Super + Shift + ,` — Dismiss all\n\n**Bindings file:** `~/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` — add/change all keybinds here.\n\n---\n\n## Common Tweaks\n\n**Rounded corners** (`~/.config/hypr/looknfeel.conf`):\n```ini\ndecoration {\n    rounding = 8\n}\n```\n\n**Remove window gaps:**\n```ini\ngeneral {\n    gaps_in = 0\n    gaps_out = 0\n    border_size = 0\n}\n```\n\n**Toggle top bar:** `Super + Shift + Space`\n\n**Caps Lock → Compose key** (default in Omarchy). To swap Caps Lock ↔ Esc instead:\n```ini\n# ~/.config/hypr/input.conf\nkb_options = caps:swapescape\n```\nTo use right alt as compose instead:\n```ini\nkb_options = compose:ralt\n```\n\n---\n\n## WireGuard / Networking (OmarchyOS specific)\n\n- `systemd-resolvconf` package required for `wg-quick` to work.\n- `fix_resolv()` must run before every `wg-quick up` to prevent DNS race conditions.\n- See Rubait's existing WireGuard setup in dotfiles for full implementation.\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting Quick Reference\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---|---|\n| Apps too large on screen | Set `env = GDK_SCALE,1` in `monitors.conf` |\n| Hyprland config broken | `hyprctl configerrors` to diagnose; `omarchy-reinstall` nuclear option |\n| Locked out (wrong password) | `Ctrl+Alt+F2` → login as root → `faillock --reset --user [username]` |\n| Update broke something | Reboot → select pre-update snapshot in bootloader |\n| Caps Lock not working | Remapped to XCompose by default — see `input.conf` |\n| `omarchy-update` fails | Check for uncommitted changes in `~/.local/share/omarchy` |\n| Speakers not working | Click speaker in Waybar → set as default with `d` in wiremix |\n| Waybar module not updating | Check signal number — 7–10 reserved, use 11+ |\n\n---\n\n## Omarchy-Specific Commands\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `omarchy-update` | Update Omarchy + packages (use instead of pacman/yay direct) |\n| `omarchy-reinstall` | Nuclear reset — restores all default configs |\n| `omarchy-debug` | Generate diagnostic output for bug reports |\n| `omarchy-restart-xcompose` | Restart XCompose after editing `~/.XCompose` |\n| `omarchy-launch-floating-terminal-with-presentation` | Waybar on-click helper for interactive scripts |\n| `hyprctl configerrors` | Check Hyprland config for errors |\n| `hyprctl reload` | Reload Hyprland config without restart |\n| `hyprctl monitors` | List connected monitors and their names |\n\n---\n\n## Rubait's Specific Config Notes\n\n- **Machine:** HP EliteDesk 800 G3 Mini — standard 1080p display → always set `GDK_SCALE=1`.\n- **OS location:** External SSD — portable, boots on multiple machines → always include `monitor=,preferred,auto,1` fallback.\n- **Shell:** bash (not zsh — `.zshrc` if present is legacy, safe to delete).\n- **Waybar signals 7–10 taken** — custom modules use 11+.\n- **Cloudflare credentials** at `/home/rubait/Documents/Obsidian Vault/cloudflare.md` — never commit.\n- **Boot scare pattern:** if `/boot` gets unmounted, UUID=C6F6-4730 is the EFI partition.\n- **Caps Lock remapped** to Esc via `caps:swapescape` in `input.conf`.\n","id":0,"bound":{"fullscreen":false,"maximized":true}}]}